</taxonomicName>
in the presence of labial and maxillary cuspules (
<figureCitation box="[267,357,1703,1727]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="13.[160,225,1062,1085]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1039]" captionTargetId="figure-220@13.[163,1153,142,1039]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 9. Idiops piluso sp. nov., holotype male (LBRE-Ar). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Labium and sternum, ventral view. (c) Eye group, dorsal view. (d) Palpal tibia, retrolateral view. (e) Leg I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181197/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="986">Figure 9</figureCitation>
(b)) and fovea almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[689,778,1703,1727]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="13.[160,225,1062,1085]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1039]" captionTargetId="figure-220@13.[163,1153,142,1039]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 9. Idiops piluso sp. nov., holotype male (LBRE-Ar). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Labium and sternum, ventral view. (c) Eye group, dorsal view. (d) Palpal tibia, retrolateral view. (e) Leg I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181197/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="986">Figure 9</figureCitation>
(a)), but can be easily separated by the straight metatarsus I and absence of an apical prolateral process. They can be distinguished from all other Argentinean species by the palpal tibia more incrassate and shorter, being wider than half of its length (less than or almost as wide as half its length in other species), retrolateral spines concentrated on the basal and apical portion of the depression, where apical spines are very long (
<figureCitation box="[524,611,1334,1358]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="13.[160,225,1062,1085]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1039]" captionTargetId="figure-220@13.[163,1153,142,1039]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 9. Idiops piluso sp. nov., holotype male (LBRE-Ar). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Labium and sternum, ventral view. (c) Eye group, dorsal view. (d) Palpal tibia, retrolateral view. (e) Leg I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181197/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="987">Figure 9</figureCitation>
(d)). Also, it can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1946" box="[1015,1092,1333,1358]" class="Arachnida" family="Idiopidae" genus="Idiops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="987" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clarus">
<emphasis box="[1015,1021,1333,1358]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="987">I</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1031,1092,1333,1358]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="987">clarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferretti &amp; Nime &amp; Mattoni, 2017" authorityName="Ferretti &amp; Nime &amp; Mattoni" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Idiopidae" genus="Idiops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="987" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minguito" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="987">I. minguito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[261,346,1368,1392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="987" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the shorter spine on apical branch of tibial apophysis and by the larger spine on the basal branch (
<figureCitation box="[454,541,1403,1427]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="13.[160,225,1062,1085]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1039]" captionTargetId="figure-220@13.[163,1153,142,1039]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 9. Idiops piluso sp. nov., holotype male (LBRE-Ar). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Labium and sternum, ventral view. (c) Eye group, dorsal view. (d) Palpal tibia, retrolateral view. (e) Leg I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181197/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="987">Figure 9</figureCitation>
(e)), palpal bulb with slightly developed apical expansion and tip of the embolus without dorsal tooth (
<figureCitation box="[653,754,1438,1462]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="14.[160,225,704,727]" captionTargetBox="[166,1142,143,671]" captionTargetId="figure-356@14.[163,1153,142,681]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 10. Idiops piluso sp. nov., holotype male (LBRE-Ar), left palpal bulb. (a) Prolateral. (b) Retrolateral. (c) Dorsal. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181199/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="987">Figure 10</figureCitation>
(a–c)). The female differs from that of the other species by the spermathecae with oval receptacles almost equal the width of the ducts, which are straight and shorter, and a slightly sclerotised basal area (
<figureCitation box="[962,1063,1507,1531]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="15.[160,225,1143,1166]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1111]" captionTargetId="figure-178@15.[163,1153,142,1112]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 11. Idiops piluso sp. nov., paratype female (MACN-Ar36721). (a) Carapace, dorsal. (b) Labium and sternum, ventral view. (c) Eye group, dorsal view. (d) Spermathecae, dorsal view. D = duct; R = receptacle; SA = sclerotised basal area. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181201/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="987">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(d)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
