<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="987" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1155,1597,1726]" box="[160,285,1597,1622]" pageId="13" pageNumber="987">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,1597,1622]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="987">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1155,1597,1726]" pageId="13" pageNumber="987">
The species is a name in apposition of ‘Capitán Piluso’, a famous TV character interpreted by 
<collectingCountry box="[194,349,1667,1691]" name="Argentina" pageId="13" pageNumber="987">the Argentine</collectingCountry>
actor Alberto Olmedo (1933–1988) during the 1960s. The character was a comic man dressed as a sailor and was an idol for children.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181199" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5181199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181199/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="988" startId="14.[160,225,704,727]" targetBox="[166,1142,143,671]" targetPageId="14">
